Nodes for Data Prep Recipes
Input Node: Add Data to the Recipe
Aggregate Node
Append Node: Stack Rows from Different Sets of Data
Filter Node: Filter Rows
Join Node: Add Related Columns of Data to the Recipe
Transform Node: Transform the Data Before Loading It Into a Target
Update Node: Swap Column Values
Output Node: Write Recipe Results to a Dataset or External System

Recipe Output to CSV

Use the Data Prep output node in CRM Analytics to save your prepared data as a data and schema file in a Salesforce BPO (storage database).
Push Data to the Salesforce Database
Pull Data from the Salesforce Database

CSV Output Considerations
An output connection is available only for recipes built with Data Prep.
Stored data is removed after 48 hours.
If the data exceeds the maximum file size or number of rows specified in the output nodeâ€™s partition settings, more than one CSV file is created.

Exporting a Dataset
When you export a dataset, a DatasetExportEvent is generated. You can subscribe to receive DatasetExportEvents. See Subscribing to Platform Events. For event reference, see DatasetExportEvent.
